37 static int C_gentity_ptr_to_entNum(unsigned long addr)
38 {
39  // no NULL address,
40  // address must also be in the range of the g_entities array memory space..
41  // address must also be pointing to the start of an entity (invalid if it points just somewhere halfway into the entity)
42  if (!addr ||
43  (gentity_t *)addr < &g_entities[0] || (gentity_t *)addr > &g_entities[MAX_GENTITIES - 1] ||
44  (addr - (unsigned long)&g_entities[0]) % sizeof(gentity_t) != 0)
45  {
46  return -1;
47  }
48  return ((gentity_t *)addr - g_entities);
49 }

518 {

522 
523  filedata = Com_Allocate(count + 1);

567 // filelist = et.trap_FS_GetFileList( dirname, fileextension )
568 extern char bigTextBuffer[100000];
569 static int _et_trap_FS_GetFileList(lua_State *L)
570 {
571  const char *dirname = luaL_checkstring(L, 1);
572  const char *filename_extension = luaL_checkstring(L, 2);
573  int newTable, index = 1, i, filelen, numfiles;
574  char filename[MAX_QPATH];
575  char *filenameptr = bigTextBuffer;
576 
577  numfiles = trap_FS_GetFileList(dirname, filename_extension, bigTextBuffer, sizeof(bigTextBuffer));
578 
579  lua_createtable(L, numfiles, 0);
580  newTable = lua_gettop(L);
581 
582  for (i = 0; i < numfiles; i++, filenameptr += filelen + 1)
583  {
584  filelen = strlen(filenameptr);
585  strcpy(filename, filenameptr);
586 
587  lua_pushstring(L, filename);
588  lua_rawseti(L, newTable, index++);
589  }
590 
591  return 1;
592 }

736  //}

738  // Check if the entity is a client
739  if (!ent->client)
740  {
741  luaL_error(L, "clientNum \"%d\" is not a client entity", clientNum);
742  return 0;
743  }
744 
745  // Check if the skill is in the range
746  if (skill < 0 || skill > SK_NUM_SKILLS - 1)
747  {
748  luaL_error(L, "\"skill\" must be a number from 0 to 6 both included");
749  return 0;
750  }
751 
752  // Check if the xp value is negative
753  if (xp < 0)
754  {
755  luaL_error(L, "negative xp values are not allowed");
756  return 0;
757  }
758 
759  // special case for 0 adds
760  if (add == 0)
761  {
762  float oldxp = ent->client->sess.skillpoints[skill];
763 
764  ent->client->sess.skillpoints[skill] = xp;
765  //ent->client->sess.mapstartSkillpoints[skill] = xp;
766  ent->client->sess.startxptotal -= oldxp;
767  ent->client->sess.startxptotal += xp;
768  }
769  else
770  {
771  ent->client->sess.skillpoints[skill] += xp;
772  //ent->client->sess.mapstartSkillpoints[skill] += xp;
773  ent->client->sess.startxptotal += xp;
774  }
775 
776  ent->client->ps.stats[STAT_XP] = (int)ent->client->sess.startxptotal;
777 
778  G_CalcRank(ent->client);
779  BG_PlayerStateToEntityState(&ent->client->ps, &ent->s, level.time, qtrue);
780 
781  return 1;
782 }

789 static int _et_G_ResetXP(lua_State *L)
790 {
791  int entnum = luaL_optinteger(L, 1, -1);
792  gentity_t *ent;
793 
794  if (entnum > -1 && entnum < MAX_CLIENTS)
795  {
796  ent = g_entities + entnum;
797 
798  if (!ent->client)
799  {
800  luaL_error(L, "clientNum \"%d\" is not a client entity", entnum);
801  return 0;
802  }
803 
804  G_ResetXP(ent);
805  }
806  else
807  {
808  luaL_error(L, "clientNum \"%d\" is not a client entity number", entnum);
809  }
810  return 0;
811 }

813 // et.AddWeaponToPlayer( clientNum, weapon, ammo, ammoclip, setcurrent )
814 static int _et_AddWeaponToPlayer(lua_State *L)
815 {
816  int clientnum = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 1);
817  gentity_t *ent = g_entities + clientnum;
818  weapon_t weapon = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 2);
819  int ammo = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 3);
820  int ammoclip = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 4);
821  int setcurrent = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 5);
822 
823  if (!ent->client)
824  {
825  luaL_error(L, "clientNum \"%d\" is not a client entity", clientnum);
826  return 0;
827  }
828 
829  if (!IS_VALID_WEAPON(weapon))
830  {
831  luaL_error(L, "weapon \"%d\" is not a valid weapon", weapon);
832  return 0;
833  }
834 
835  COM_BitSet(ent->client->ps.weapons, weapon);
836  ent->client->ps.ammoclip[GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->clipIndex] = ammoclip;
837  ent->client->ps.ammo[GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->ammoIndex] = ammo;
838 
839  if (setcurrent == 1)
840  {
841  ent->client->ps.weapon = weapon;
842  }
843 
844 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
845  Bot_Event_AddWeapon(ent->client->ps.clientNum, Bot_WeaponGameToBot(weapon));
846 #endif
847 
848  return 1;
849 }

851 // et.RemoveWeaponFromPlayer( clientNum, weapon )
852 static int _et_RemoveWeaponFromPlayer(lua_State *L)
853 {
854  int clientnum = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 1);
855  gentity_t *ent = g_entities + clientnum;
856  gclient_t *client = ent->client;
857  weapon_t weapon = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 2);
858 
859  if (!ent->client)
860  {
861  luaL_error(L, "clientNum \"%d\" is not a client entity", clientnum);
862  return 0;
863  }
864 
865  COM_BitClear(ent->client->ps.weapons, weapon);
866 
867  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->weapAlts)
868  {
869  weapon_t weapAlts = GetWeaponTableData(weapon)->weapAlts;
870 
871  if (GetWeaponTableData(weapAlts)->type & (WEAPON_TYPE_RIFLENADE | WEAPON_TYPE_SCOPED | WEAPON_TYPE_SET))
872  {
873  COM_BitClear(client->ps.weapons, weapAlts);
874  }
875  }
876 
877  // Clear out empty weapon, change to next best weapon
878  G_AddEvent(ent, EV_WEAPONSWITCHED, 0);
879 
880  if (weapon == client->ps.weapon)
881  {
882  client->ps.weapon = 0;
883  }
884 
885 #ifdef FEATURE_OMNIBOT
886  Bot_Event_RemoveWeapon(client->ps.clientNum, Bot_WeaponGameToBot(weapon));
887 #endif
888 
889  return 1;
890 }

892 // et.GetCurrentWeapon( clientNum ) -> weapon, ammo, ammoclip
893 static int _et_GetCurrentWeapon(lua_State *L)
894 {
895  gentity_t *ent;
896  gclient_t *client;
897  int clientNum, ammo, ammoclip;
898 
899  clientNum = luaL_checkinteger(L, 1);
900  if (clientNum < 0 || clientNum >= MAX_CLIENTS)
901  {
902  luaL_error(L, "\"clientNum\" is out of bounds: %d", clientNum);
903  }
904 
905  ent = g_entities + clientNum;
906  if (!ent->client)
907  {
908  luaL_error(L, "\"clientNum\" \"%d\" is not a client entity", clientNum);
909  }
910 
911  client = ent->client;
912  ammo = client->ps.ammo[GetWeaponTableData(client->ps.weapon)->ammoIndex];
913  ammoclip = client->ps.ammoclip[GetWeaponTableData(client->ps.weapon)->clipIndex];
914 
915  lua_pushinteger(L, client->ps.weapon);
916  lua_pushinteger(L, ammo);
917  lua_pushinteger(L, ammoclip);
918 
919  return 3;
920 }

1315 gentity_t *G_Lua_CreateEntity(char *params)
1316 {
1317  gentity_t *create;
1318  char *token;
1319  char *p = params;
1320  char key[MAX_TOKEN_CHARS], value[MAX_TOKEN_CHARS];
1321 
1322  level.numSpawnVars = 0;
1323  level.numSpawnVarChars = 0;
1324 
1325  while (1)
1326  {
1327  token = COM_ParseExt(&p, qfalse);
1328  if (!token[0])
1329  {
1330  break;
1331  }
1332  strcpy(key, token);
1333 
1334  token = COM_ParseExt(&p, qfalse);
1335  if (!token[0])
1336  {
1337  // note: we migth do more than a simple return here
1338  // nextmap?
1339  G_Printf("%s API: spawn key \"%s\" has no valu\n", LUA_VERSION, key);
1340  return NULL;
1341  }
1342 
1343  strcpy(value, token);
1344 
1345  if (g_scriptDebug.integer)
1346  {
1347  G_Printf("%s API %d: set [%s] [%s] [%s]\n", LUA_VERSION, level.time, GAMEVERSION, key, value);
1348  }
1349 
1350  if (level.numSpawnVars == MAX_SPAWN_VARS)
1351  {
1352  // see above note
1353  G_Printf("%s API: can't spawn an entity - MAX_SPAWN_VARS reached.\n", LUA_VERSION);
1354  return NULL;
1355  }
1356 
1357  level.spawnVars[level.numSpawnVars][0] = G_AddSpawnVarToken(key);
1358  level.spawnVars[level.numSpawnVars][1] = G_AddSpawnVarToken(value);
1359 
1360  level.numSpawnVars++;
1361  }
1362  create = G_SpawnGEntityFromSpawnVars();
1363 
1364  //create->classname = "lua_spawn"; // make additional param?
1365 
1366  if (!create) // don't link NULL ents
1367  {
1368  return NULL;
1369  }
1370 
1371  trap_LinkEntity(create);
1372  return create;
1373 }

1472 // spawnval = et.G_GetSpawnVar( entnum, key )
1473 // This function works with fields ( g_spawn.c @ 72 )
1474 //
1475 // Description:
1476 // The mapper, using his map-editor, assigns spawnvars.
1477 // Spawnvars, and their values, are represented in code as members of gentity_t.
1478 // Spawnvar names can be different from the corresponding gentity_t membernames.
1479 // For example the spawnvar "shortname" is used with trigger_objective_info entities in the map-editor,
1480 // while in code the gentity_t membername is "message"..
1481 // This function _et_G_GetSpawnVar() returns the value of a gentity_t member,
1482 // where the argument is a spawnvar name.
1483 // (the array called "fields" in g_spawn.c is a mapping of spawnvars<->members)
1484 static int _et_G_GetSpawnVar(lua_State *L)
1485 {
1486  gentity_t *ent;
1487  int entnum = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 1);
1488  const char *key = luaL_checkstring(L, 2);
1489  int index = GetFieldIndex(key);
1490  fieldtype_t type = GetFieldType(key);
1491  int ofs;
1492 
1493  // break on invalid gentity field
1494  if (index == -1)
1495  {
1496  luaL_error(L, "field \"%s\" index is -1", key);
1497  return 0;
1498  }
1499 
1500  if (entnum < 0 || entnum >= MAX_GENTITIES)
1501  {
1502  luaL_error(L, "entnum \"%d\" is out of range", entnum);
1503  return 0;
1504  }
1505 
1506  ent = &g_entities[entnum];
1507 
1508  // If the entity is not in use, return nil
1509  if (!ent->inuse)
1510  {
1511  lua_pushnil(L);
1512  return 1;
1513  }
1514 
1515  ofs = fields[index].ofs;
1516 
1517  switch (type)
1518  {
1519  case F_INT:
1520  lua_pushinteger(L, *(int *) ((byte *)ent + ofs));
1521  return 1;
1522  case F_FLOAT:
1523  lua_pushnumber(L, *(float *) ((byte *)ent + ofs));
1524  return 1;
1525  case F_LSTRING:
1526  case F_GSTRING:
1527  if (fields[index].flags & FIELD_FLAG_NOPTR)
1528  {
1529  lua_pushstring(L, (char *) ((byte *)ent + ofs));
1530  }
1531  else
1532  {
1533  lua_pushstring(L, *(char **) ((byte *)ent + ofs));
1534  }
1535  return 1;
1536  case F_VECTOR:
1537  case F_ANGLEHACK:
1538  _et_gentity_getvec3(L, *(vec3_t *)((byte *)ent + ofs));
1539  return 1;
1540  case F_ENTITY:
1541  {
1542  // return the entity-number of the entity that the pointer is pointing at.
1543  int entNum = C_gentity_ptr_to_entNum(*(int *)((byte *)ent + ofs));
1544 
1545  if (entNum < 0)
1546  {
1547  lua_pushnil(L);
1548  }
1549  else
1550  {
1551  lua_pushinteger(L, entNum);
1552  }
1553  }
1554  return 1;
1555  case F_ITEM:
1556  case F_CLIENT:
1557  case F_IGNORE:
1558  default:
1559  lua_pushnil(L);
1560  return 1;
1561  }
1562  return 0;
1563 }

1642 // variable = et.gentity_get( entnum, fieldname, arrayindex )
1643 static int _et_gentity_get(lua_State *L)
1644 {
1645  gentity_t *ent = g_entities + (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 1);
1646  const char *fieldname = luaL_checkstring(L, 2);
1647  gentity_field_t *field = _et_gentity_getfield(ent, (char *)fieldname);
1648  unsigned long addr;
1649 
1650  // break on invalid gentity field
1651  if (!field)
1652  {
1653  luaL_error(L, "tried to get invalid gentity field \"%s\"", fieldname);
1654  return 0;
1655  }
1656 
1657  if (field->flags & FIELD_FLAG_GENTITY)
1658  {
1659  addr = (unsigned long)ent;
1660  }
1661  else
1662  {
1663  addr = (unsigned long)ent->client;
1664  }
1665 
1666  // for NULL entities, return nil (prevents server crashes!)
1667  if (!addr)
1668  {
1669  lua_pushnil(L);
1670  return 1;
1671  }
1672 
1673  addr += field->mapping;
1674 
1675  switch (field->type)
1676  {
1677  case FIELD_INT:
1678  lua_pushinteger(L, *(int *)addr);
1679  return 1;
1680  case FIELD_STRING:
1681  if (field->flags & FIELD_FLAG_NOPTR)
1682  {
1683  lua_pushstring(L, (char *)addr);
1684  }
1685  else
1686  {
1687  lua_pushstring(L, *(char **)addr);
1688  }
1689  return 1;
1690  case FIELD_FLOAT:
1691  lua_pushnumber(L, *(float *)addr);
1692  return 1;
1693  case FIELD_ENTITY:
1694  {
1695  // core: return the entity-number of the entity that the pointer is pointing at.
1696  int entNum = C_gentity_ptr_to_entNum(*(int *)addr);
1697 
1698  if (entNum < 0)
1699  {
1700  lua_pushnil(L);
1701  }
1702  else
1703  {
1704  lua_pushinteger(L, entNum);
1705  }
1706  }
1707  return 1;
1708  case FIELD_VEC3:
1709  _et_gentity_getvec3(L, *(vec3_t *)addr);
1710  return 1;
1711  case FIELD_INT_ARRAY:
1712  lua_pushinteger(L, (*(int *)(addr + (sizeof(int) * (int)luaL_optinteger(L, 3, 0)))));
1713  return 1;
1714  case FIELD_TRAJECTORY:
1715  _et_gentity_gettrajectory(L, (trajectory_t *)addr);
1716  return 1;
1717  case FIELD_FLOAT_ARRAY:
1718  lua_pushnumber(L, (*(float *)(addr + (sizeof(int) * (int)luaL_optinteger(L, 3, 0)))));
1719  return 1;
1720  case FIELD_WEAPONSTAT:
1721  _et_gentity_getweaponstat(L, (weapon_stat_t *)(addr + (sizeof(weapon_stat_t) * (int)luaL_optinteger(L, 3, 0))));
1722  return 1;
1723 
1724  }
1725  return 0;
1726 }

1739  {
1740  luaL_error(L, "tried to set invalid gentity field \"%s\"", fieldname);
1741  return 0;
1742  }
1743 
1744  // break on read-only gentity field
1745  if (field->flags & FIELD_FLAG_READONLY)
1746  {
1747  luaL_error(L, "tried to set read-only gentity field \"%s\"", fieldname);
1748  return 0;
1749  }
1750 
1751  if (field->flags & FIELD_FLAG_GENTITY)
1752  {
1753  addr = (unsigned long)ent;
1754  }
1755  else
1756  {
1757  addr = (unsigned long)ent->client;
1758  }
1759 
1760  // for NULL entities, return nil (prevents server crashes!)
1761  if (!addr)
1762  {
1763  lua_pushnil(L);
1764  return 1;
1765  }
1766 
1767  addr += field->mapping;
1768 
1769  switch (field->type)
1770  {
1771  case FIELD_INT:
1772  *(int *)addr = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 3);
1773  break;
1774  case FIELD_STRING:
1775  buffer = luaL_checkstring(L, 3);
1776  if (field->flags & FIELD_FLAG_NOPTR)
1777  {
1778  Q_strncpyz((char *)addr, buffer, strlen((char *)addr));
1779  }
1780  else
1781  {
1782  Com_Dealloc(*(char **)addr);
1783  *(char **)addr = Com_Allocate(strlen(buffer) + 1);
1784  Q_strncpyz(*(char **)addr, buffer, strlen(buffer));
1785  }
1786  break;
1787  case FIELD_FLOAT:
1788  *(float *)addr = (float)luaL_checknumber(L, 3);
1789  break;
1790  case FIELD_ENTITY:
1791  // pointer-fields are read-only..
1792  break;
1793  case FIELD_VEC3:
1794  _et_gentity_setvec3(L, (vec3_t *)addr);
1795  break;
1796  case FIELD_INT_ARRAY:
1797  *(int *)(addr + (sizeof(int) * (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 3))) = (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 4);
1798  break;
1799  case FIELD_TRAJECTORY:
1800  _et_gentity_settrajectory(L, (trajectory_t *)addr);
1801  break;
1802  case FIELD_FLOAT_ARRAY:
1803  *(float *)(addr + (sizeof(int) * (int)luaL_checkinteger(L, 3))) = luaL_checknumber(L, 4);
1804  return 1;
1805  default:
1806  G_Printf("Lua API: et.gentity_set with no valid field type\n");
1807  break;
1808  }
1809  return 0;
1810 }

2102 /*
2103  * G_LuaRunIsolated(modName)
2104  * Creates and runs specified module in isolated state
2105  */
2106 qboolean G_LuaRunIsolated(const char *modName)
2107 {
2108  int freeVM, flen = 0;
2109  static char allowedModules[MAX_CVAR_VALUE_STRING];
2110  char *code, *signature;
2111  fileHandle_t f;
2112  lua_vm_t *vm;
2113 
2114  for (freeVM = 0; freeVM < LUA_NUM_VM; freeVM++)
2115  {
2116  if (lVM[freeVM] == NULL)
2117  {
2118  break;
2119  }
2120  }
2121 
2122  if (freeVM == LUA_NUM_VM)
2123  {
2124  G_Printf("%s API: %sno free VMs left to load module: \"%s\" \n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, modName);
2125  return qfalse;
2126  }
2127 
2128  Q_strncpyz(allowedModules, Q_strupr(lua_allowedModules.string), sizeof(allowedModules));
2129 
2130  // try to open lua file
2131  flen = trap_FS_FOpenFile(modName, &f, FS_READ);
2132  if (flen < 0)
2133  {
2134  G_Printf("%s API: %scan not open file '%s'\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, modName);
2135  }
2136  else if (flen > LUA_MAX_FSIZE)
2137  {
2138  // Let's not load arbitrarily big files to memory.
2139  // If your lua file exceeds the limit, let me know.
2140  G_Printf("%s API: %signoring file '%s' (too big)\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, modName);
2141  trap_FS_FCloseFile(f);
2142  }
2143  else
2144  {
2145  code = Com_Allocate(flen + 1);
2146 
2147  if (code == NULL)
2148  {
2149  G_Error("%s API: %smemory allocation error for '%s' data\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, modName);
2150  }
2151 
2152  trap_FS_Read(code, flen, f);
2153  *(code + flen) = '\0';
2154  trap_FS_FCloseFile(f);
2155  signature = G_SHA1(code);
2156 
2157  if (Q_stricmp(lua_allowedModules.string, "") && !strstr(allowedModules, signature))
2158  {
2159  // don't load disallowed lua modules into vm
2160  Com_Dealloc(code); // fixed memory leaking in Lua API - thx ETPub/goesa
2161  G_Printf("%s API: %sLua module [%s] [%s] disallowed by ACL\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, modName, signature);
2162  }
2163  else
2164  {
2165  // Init lua_vm_t struct
2166  vm = (lua_vm_t *)Com_Allocate(sizeof(lua_vm_t));
2167 
2168  if (vm == NULL)
2169  {
2170  G_Error("%s API: %svm memory allocation error for %s data\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, modName);
2171  }
2172 
2173  vm->id = -1;
2174  Q_strncpyz(vm->file_name, modName, sizeof(vm->file_name));
2175  Q_strncpyz(vm->mod_name, "", sizeof(vm->mod_name));
2176  Q_strncpyz(vm->mod_signature, signature, sizeof(vm->mod_signature));
2177  vm->code = code;
2178  vm->code_size = flen;
2179  vm->err = 0;
2180 
2181  // Start lua virtual machine
2182  if (G_LuaStartVM(vm))
2183  {
2184  vm->id = freeVM;
2185  lVM[freeVM] = vm;
2186  return qtrue;
2187  }
2188  else
2189  {
2190  G_LuaStopVM(vm);
2191  }
2192  }
2193  }
2194  return qfalse;
2195 }

2315  {
2316  G_Printf("%s API: %smemory allocation error\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE);

2320  Q_strncpyz(vm->file_name, "current API available to scripts", sizeof(vm->file_name));
2321  vm->code = "";
2322  vm->code_size = 0;

2326  if (G_LuaStartVM(vm))

2333  G_Printf("%s API: %serror - et prefix is not correctly registered\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE);
2334  }

2336  {

2338 
2339  G_Printf("----------------------------------------------------------------\n");
2340  G_Printf("%-42s%-17s%-10s\n", "Name", "Type", "Value");
2341  G_Printf("----------------------------------------------------------------\n");

2343  // et namespace
2344  for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_LEN(types); i++)
2345  {
2346  lua_pushnil(L); // stack now contains: -1 => nil; -2 => table
2347  while (lua_next(L, -2))
2348  {
2349  // order by variable data type
2350  if (lua_type(L, -1) == types[i])
2351  {
2352  G_Printf("et.%-39s^%i%-17s^7%-10s\n", lua_tostring(L, -2), i, lua_typename(L, lua_type(L, -1)), (lua_isfunction(L, -1) ? "N/A" : lua_tostring(L, -1)));
2353  }
2354  lua_pop(L, 1);
2355  }
2356  }
2357  // globals
2358  lua_pushglobaltable(L);
2359  lua_pushnil(L);
2360  while (lua_next(L, -2))
2361  {
2362  if (lua_type(L, -1) == LUA_TSTRING)
2363  {
2364  G_Printf("%-42s^8%-17s^7%-10s\n", lua_tostring(L, -2), "global string", lua_tostring(L, -1));
2365  }
2366  lua_pop(L, 1);
2367  }
2368  }
2369  }
2370  lua_close(vm->L);
2371  vm->L = NULL;
2372  Com_Dealloc(vm);
2373 }

2799 /*
2800  * G_LuaStartVM( vm )
2801  * Starts one individual virtual machine.
2802  */
2803 qboolean G_LuaStartVM(lua_vm_t *vm)
2804 {
2805  int res;
2806  char basepath[MAX_OSPATH];
2807  char homepath[MAX_OSPATH];
2808  char gamepath[MAX_OSPATH];
2809  const char *luaPath, *luaCPath;
2810 
2811  // Open a new lua state
2812  vm->L = luaL_newstate();
2813  if (!vm->L)
2814  {
2815  G_Printf("%s API: %sLua failed to initialise.\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE);
2816  return qfalse;
2817  }
2818 
2819  // Initialise the lua state
2820  luaL_openlibs(vm->L);
2821 
2822 #ifdef FEATURE_LUASQL
2823  // register LuaSQL backend
2824  luaL_getsubtable(vm->L, LUA_REGISTRYINDEX, "_PRELOAD");
2825  lua_pushcfunction(vm->L, luaopen_luasql_sqlite3);
2826  lua_setfield(vm->L, -2, "luasql.sqlite3");
2827  lua_pop(vm->L, 1);
2828 #endif
2829 
2830  // set LUA_PATH and LUA_CPATH
2831  trap_Cvar_VariableStringBuffer("fs_basepath", basepath, sizeof(basepath));
2832  trap_Cvar_VariableStringBuffer("fs_homepath", homepath, sizeof(homepath));
2833  trap_Cvar_VariableStringBuffer("fs_game", gamepath, sizeof(gamepath));
2834 
2835  luaPath = va("%s%s%s%s?.lua;%s%s%s%slualibs%s?.lua",
2836  homepath, LUA_DIRSEP, gamepath, LUA_DIRSEP,
2837  homepath, LUA_DIRSEP, gamepath, LUA_DIRSEP, LUA_DIRSEP);
2838 
2839  luaCPath = va("%s%s%s%slualibs%s?.%s",
2840  homepath, LUA_DIRSEP, gamepath, LUA_DIRSEP, LUA_DIRSEP, EXTENSION);
2841 
2842  // add fs_basepath if different from fs_homepath
2843  if (Q_stricmp(basepath, homepath))
2844  {
2845  luaPath = va("%s%s%s%s?.lua;%s%s%s%slualibs%s?.lua;%s",
2846  basepath, LUA_DIRSEP, gamepath, LUA_DIRSEP,
2847  basepath, LUA_DIRSEP, gamepath, LUA_DIRSEP, LUA_DIRSEP, luaPath);
2848 
2849  luaCPath = va("%s%s%s%slualibs%s?.%s;%s",
2850  basepath, LUA_DIRSEP, gamepath, LUA_DIRSEP, LUA_DIRSEP, EXTENSION,
2851  luaCPath);
2852  }
2853 
2854  lua_getglobal(vm->L, LUA_LOADLIBNAME);
2855  if (lua_istable(vm->L, -1))
2856  {
2857  lua_pushstring(vm->L, luaPath);
2858  lua_setfield(vm->L, -2, "path");
2859  lua_pushstring(vm->L, luaCPath);
2860  lua_setfield(vm->L, -2, "cpath");
2861  }
2862  lua_pop(vm->L, 1);
2863 
2864  // register globals
2865  lua_registerglobal(vm->L, "LUA_PATH", luaPath);
2866  lua_registerglobal(vm->L, "LUA_CPATH", luaCPath);
2867 
2868  lua_registerglobal(vm->L, "LUA_DIRSEP", LUA_DIRSEP);
2869 
2870  // register functions
2871  luaL_newlib(vm->L, etlib);
2872 
2873  // register predefined constants
2874  registerConstants(vm);
2875 
2876  lua_pushvalue(vm->L, -1);
2877  lua_setglobal(vm->L, "et");
2878 
2879  res = luaL_loadbuffer(vm->L, vm->code, vm->code_size, vm->file_name);
2880 
2881  switch (res)
2882  {
2883  case LUA_OK:
2884  break;
2885  case LUA_ERRSYNTAX:
2886  G_Printf("%s API: %ssyntax error during pre-compilation: %s\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, lua_tostring(vm->L, -1));
2887  lua_pop(vm->L, 1);
2888  vm->err++;
2889  return qfalse;
2890  case LUA_ERRMEM:
2891  G_Printf("%s API: %smemory allocation error #1 ( %s )\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, vm->file_name);
2892  vm->err++;
2893  return qfalse;
2894  case LUA_ERRGCMM:
2895  G_Printf("%s API: %serror while running a __gc metamethod caused by garbage collector ( %s )\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, vm->file_name);
2896  vm->err++;
2897  return qfalse;
2898  default:
2899  G_Printf("%s API: %sunknown error %i ( %s )\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, res, vm->file_name);
2900  vm->err++;
2901  return qfalse;
2902  }
2903 
2904  // Execute the code
2905  if (!G_LuaCall(vm, "G_LuaStartVM", 0, 0))
2906  {
2907  G_Printf("%s API: %sLua VM start failed ( %s )\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, vm->file_name);
2908  return qfalse;
2909  }
2910 
2911  // Load the code
2912  G_Printf("%s API: %sfile '%s' loaded into Lua VM\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, vm->file_name);
2913 
2914  return qtrue;
2915 }

2918  * G_LuaStopVM( vm )
2919  * Stops one virtual machine, and calls its et_Quit callback.
2920  */
2921 void G_LuaStopVM(lua_vm_t *vm)
2922 {
2923  if (vm == NULL)
2924  {
2925  return;
2926  }
2927  if (vm->code != NULL)
2928  {
2929  Com_Dealloc(vm->code);
2930  vm->code = NULL;
2931  }
2932  if (vm->L)
2933  {
2934  if (G_LuaGetNamedFunction(vm, "et_Quit"))
2935  {
2936  G_LuaCall(vm, "et_Quit", 0, 0);
2937  }
2938  lua_close(vm->L);
2939  vm->L = NULL;
2940  }
2941  if (vm->id >= 0)
2942  {
2943  if (lVM[vm->id] == vm)
2944  {
2945  lVM[vm->id] = NULL;
2946  }
2947  if (!vm->err)
2948  {
2949  G_Printf("%s API: %sLua module [%s] [%s] unloaded.\n", LUA_VERSION, S_COLOR_BLUE, vm->file_name, vm->mod_signature);
2950  }
2951  }
2952  Com_Dealloc(vm);
2953 }
